    <a title="Kayla Edwards" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/24780999-kayla-edwards"><img alt="Kayla Edwards" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1411656250p2/24780999.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/743565038?book_show_action=true">Oct 17, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kayla Edwards" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kayla Edwards" href="/user/show/24780999-kayla-edwards">Kayla Edwards</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/24780999-kayla-edwards?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/24780999-kayla-edwards?shelf=young-adult-novels">young-adult-novels</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer743565038" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15583448981287056112">We find Daja in Namon - a place so cold that the primary form of travel is ice skating for much of the year. Daja is completely caught up in helping the twins, whose magic she just discovered, to harness and control their powers when house fires begin to mysteriously become more and more frequent. She begins to work closely with local firefighting expert, Bennat Ladradun, to find the fire bug responsible for these heinous acts but will her search lead Daja to something she is not prepared to fac</span>
  <span id="freeText15583448981287056112" style="display:none">We find Daja in Namon - a place so cold that the primary form of travel is ice skating for much of the year. Daja is completely caught up in helping the twins, whose magic she just discovered, to harness and control their powers when house fires begin to mysteriously become more and more frequent. She begins to work closely with local firefighting expert, Bennat Ladradun, to find the fire bug responsible for these heinous acts but will her search lead Daja to something she is not prepared to face?<br /><br />I have honestly lost count of how many times I've read and reread this series. I keep trying to remember but it's just not happening. I won't lie to you - this one tore me up pretty bad. I hurt so much for Daja every time I read this one and it never gets any better. Wonderfully done, wonderfully heartbreaking. Definitely recommended.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15583448981287056112" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
